Events.RelatedBody:
**Description**

System.Xml.XmlException is thrown when opening a word document that is created by DocumentFormat.OpenXml that contains an empty URI.

**Information**

- .NET Target: Observed on .NET 4.5.2 and 4.7.2
- DocumentFormat.OpenXml Version: 2.12.0

**Repro**

```csharp
using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using DocumentFormat.OpenXml;
using DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging;
using DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Validation;
using DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Wordprocessing;

namespace ConsoleApp5
{
    internal class Program
    {
        private static void Main()
        {
            using (var wordDocument = WordprocessingDocument.Create("test.docx", WordprocessingDocumentType.Document))
            {
                var mainPart = wordDocument.AddMainDocumentPart();
                mainPart.Document = new Document();
                var body = mainPart.Document.AppendChild(new Body());

                var link = mainPart.AddHyperlinkRelationship(new Uri("", UriKind.RelativeOrAbsolute), true);
                body.AppendChild(new Paragraph(new Hyperlink(new Run(new Text("empty URI link"))) {Id = link.Id}));

                var validator = new OpenXmlValidator();
                var errors = validator.Validate(wordDocument);
                foreach (var error in errors)
                {
                    // in this repro, no validation errors occur
                    Debug.Fail($"Document validation error. {error.Description} on node: {error.Node}");
                }
            }

            // System.Xml.XmlException occurs while opening
            using (var wordDocument = WordprocessingDocument.Open("test.docx", false))
            {
                var body = wordDocument.MainDocumentPart.Document.Body;
            }
        }
    }
}
``` 

Alternately, the following test case, similar to https://github.com/OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK/blob/d2da627a33cf40b0439c4e60465de5c51bfdf2d4/test/DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Tests/ofapiTest/OpenXmlPartTest.cs#L97-L165:
```csharp
        [Fact]
        public void HyperlinkRelationshipTest3()
        {
            using (var stream = new MemoryStream())
            {
                using (var testDocument = WordprocessingDocument.Create(stream, WordprocessingDocumentType.Document))
                {
                    var mainPart = testDocument.AddMainDocumentPart();
                    mainPart.Document = new Document();
                    var body = mainPart.Document.AppendChild(new Body());

                    var link = mainPart.AddHyperlinkRelationship(new System.Uri(string.Empty, System.UriKind.RelativeOrAbsolute), true);
                    body.AppendChild(new Paragraph(new Hyperlink(new Run(new Text("empty URI link"))) {Id = link.Id}));

                    var validator = new OpenXmlValidator();
                    var errors = validator.Validate(testDocument);
                    Assert.Empty(errors);
                }

                stream.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);
                // System.Xml.XmlException occurs while opening
                using (var wordDocument = WordprocessingDocument.Open(stream, false))
                {
                    Assert.Single(wordDocument.MainDocumentPart.HyperlinkRelationships);
                }
            }
        }
```

**Observed**

System.Xml.XmlException: Relationship tag requires attribute 'Target'. Line 1, position 124.
   at MS.Internal.IO.Packaging.InternalRelationshipCollection.ProcessRelationshipAttributes(XmlCompatibilityReader reader)
   at MS.Internal.IO.Packaging.InternalRelationshipCollection.ParseRelationshipPart(PackagePart part)
   at MS.Internal.IO.Packaging.InternalRelationshipCollection..ctor(Package package, PackagePart part)
   at System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.EnsureRelationships()
   at System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.GetRelationshipsHelper(String filterString)
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.PackagePartRelationshipPropertyCollection..ctor(PackagePart packagePart)
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.OpenXmlPart.Load(OpenXmlPackage openXmlPackage, OpenXmlPart parent, Uri uriTarget, String id, Dictionary\`2 loadedParts)
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.OpenXmlPartContainer.LoadReferencedPartsAndRelationships(OpenXmlPackage openXmlPackage, OpenXmlPart sourcePart, RelationshipCollection relationshipCollection, Dictionary\`2 loadedParts)
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.OpenXmlPackage.Load()
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.OpenXmlPackage.OpenCore(String path, Boolean readWriteMode)
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.WordprocessingDocument.Open(String path, Boolean isEditable, OpenSettings openSettings)
   at DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging.WordprocessingDocument.Open(String path, Boolean isEditable)
   at ConsoleApp5.Program.Main() in Program.cs:line 33

I believe this is the offending xml, from `document.xml.rels`:
`<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Relationships xmlns="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/package/2006/relationships">
    <Relationship Type="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships/hyperlink" Target="" TargetMode="External" Id="Re5bd9f7c50024f46" />
</Relationships>`

**Expected**

Xml Validator warning and/or document opened.

**Description**

When converting from a .docx format to a .dotx format, the images contained in the document show "The linked image cannot be displayed. The file may have been moved, renamed, or deleted. Verify that the link points to the correct file and location".

When inspecting the generated XML and comparing to a manually saved .dotx, it appears the image loses an r:href attribute.

**Information**

- .NET Target: .NET Framework & .NET Core...untested in others
- DocumentFormat.OpenXml Version: 2.12.0

**Repro**

Create a console application, and add a folder named "files". Create a .docx file in this folder named "Doc1.docx", the document should contain an image. Change the Build Action on the file to Content and Copy Always. Run the application. Open the .dotx that is created in the executing bin\files folder. The image is missing.

```csharp
using DocumentFormat.OpenXml.Packaging;
using System.IO;

namespace ConsoleApp1
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            var root = Path.Combine(Path.GetDirectoryName(System.Reflection.Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().Location), "files");

            File.Copy(@$"{root}\Doc1.docx", @$"{root}\Doc2.docx");
            using (var doc = WordprocessingDocument.Open(@$"{root}\Doc2.docx", true))
            {
                doc.ChangeDocumentType(DocumentFormat.OpenXml.WordprocessingDocumentType.Template);

                doc.SaveAs(@$"{root}\Doc1.dotx").Close();
                doc.Close();
            }
            File.Delete(@$"{root}\Doc2.docx");
        }
    }
}

``` 

**Observed**

Images are not displayed correctly in the .dotx

**Expected**

Images should be displayed in the .dotx

